// TO check the parameter in sql mode
show parameter parameter name;

// it shows the value which we need to changed to check the reflection or change for paremeter open_cursors.
show parameter open_cursors;   //output integer value is "300"

To check SP&P file we need to chnage the directory to dbs from oracle_home and then command : ls- lrt
initproddb.ora---P file
spfileproddb.ora--sp file

ALTER SYSTEM SET OPEN_CURSORS=500 SCOPE=SPFILE;
after altered check the parameter using 5 th line. //output will be the same "300".
we cannot see any change reflection in the memory as scope =sp file to see the change 
shutdown immediate;
startup;
show parameter OPEN_CURSORS;
//output integer value will be "500".

ALTER SYSTEM SET OPEN_CURSORS=700 SCOPE=memory;
after altered check the parameter using 5 th line. //output will be the same "500".
we can see the change reflection in the memory as scope ="memory" 
shutdown immediate;
startup;
show parameter OPEN_CURSORS;
//output integer value will be "300".
beacause when ever we shutdowm the instance will disconnect with database and started with new instance.

ALTER SYSTEM SET OPEN_CURSORS=700 SCOPE=both;
after altered check the parameter using 5 th line. //output will be the same "700".
we can see any change reflection in the memory as scope =both to see the change in system
shutdown immediate;
startup;
show parameter OPEN_CURSORS;
//output integer value will be "700".

we can create sp file using p file.
create spfile from pfile;
create pfile from spfile;
we lost both we can create using memory
create spfile from memory;




